    "collapsible_content_2_hrRGJn": {
      "type": "collapsible-content-2",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_tab_tBJXhQ": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "IRREGULAR PERIODS OR PCOS?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Up to <strong>80% of women with PCOS have insulin resistance</strong>. Inositol helps restore ovulation and balance hormones—<strong>85% saw their cycles return</strong>, and cycle length dropped by <strong>54%</strong> in studies.*</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_zJaULT": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "CRAVINGS AND BLOOD SUGAR DIPS?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Blood sugar spikes, cravings, and energy crashes are signs your metabolism may be out of sync. Inositol supports <strong>healthy glucose metabolism</strong>—so you feel more balanced throughout the day. In one trial, it helped reduce cravings, improve fat loss by <strong>35% more than diet alone</strong>, and preserved <strong>7.1% lean muscle</strong>.*</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_EHUzbD": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "MOOD SWINGS AND ANXIETY?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>If your mood feels unpredictable or you’re constantly on edge, it might not “just be hormones”—<strong>it could be your metabolism</strong>.<strong> </strong>A meta-analysis linked inositol to <strong>improved mood</strong>, with positive effects for <strong>PMDD</strong>, <strong>anxiety</strong>, and <strong>emotional balance</strong>.*</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_AmTzjg": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "ON THE PILL BUT STILL FEEL OFF?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>The pill can provide temporary relief, but does not fix the root cause. Inositol supports natural hormone balance. <strong>Ovulation returned in 62.5%</strong> within 3 months and <strong>testosterone dropped</strong> significantly in PCOS studies.*</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_9mhfxD": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "FERTILITY STRUGGLES?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>It’s not just hormones—<strong>insulin resistance</strong> impacts fertility too. Inositol improved egg quality by <strong>46%</strong>, and <strong>pregnancy rates rose by 34%</strong> in IVF patients.*</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_xVREzb": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "LOW ENERGY AND CRASHES?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Constant fatigue? It could be blood sugar chaos. Inositol <strong>cut fasting insulin by 25%</strong> and improved insulin resistance markers by <strong>45%</strong>, leading to steadier energy thoughout the day.*</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
